      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 528: Switching from createCommit(announce\u003dtrue) to commitCollabUpdate() means the persisted snapshot is no longer announced; peers only pick up the side ref on their *next* incidental fetch. If the local device goes offline shortly after this debounced persist (and there is no further conversation activity to trigger a sync), the snapshot may not reach any peer for a long time, weakening the \u0027survives a daemon restart on the receiving side\u0027 guarantee this change is built around. Consider triggering a lightweight sync/fetch of refs/collab/* after persisting (without adding a visible commit) so propagation isn\u0027t purely best-effort.",
      "revId": "9036a80c9f19ecb988eb661db80386df976199c4",
