      "side": 1,
      "message": "[info] Line 1898: The legacy full-history scan (convCommitsToMap(log(options))) now runs on every collaborativeCommits() call even for documents that were created after the migration and therefore only ever have data on side refs. For conversations with long histories this is an O(history) walk that yields nothing in the common case. Since side-ref reads are cheap, consider only falling back to the legacy scan when the document has no side-ref results, or otherwise gating it, to avoid paying the walk for every new-storage document open.",
